    "body": "I'm so, sorry. I was not able to see VI mode precisely because of my Set-PSReadLineOption -ViModeChangeHandler was messing things up.\r\n\r\nDeleting this config from my profile now has powershell VI mode indicator working:\r\n\r\n```powershell\r\nfunction OnViModeChange\r\n{\r\n    if ($args[0] -eq 'Command')\r\n    {\r\n        # Set the cursor to a blinking block.\r\n        Write-Host -NoNewline \"`e[1 q\"\r\n    } else\r\n    {\r\n        # Set the cursor to a blinking line.\r\n        Write-Host -NoNewline \"`e[5 q\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\nSet-PSReadLineOption -ViModeIndicator Script -ViModeChangeHandler $Function:OnViModeChange\r\n```\r\n\r\nSorry for the wasted issue! Thanks for this amazing project!",
